  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 4.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And commanded Judah to seek the Lord God of their fathers.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " What an indication lies couched in this word \"commanded\" (confirmatory of the spirit of what is said above, in our previous verse-note) of the moral efforts of Asa, and that the efforts on which he may have largely relied for \"taking away the high places\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "were moral",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " efforts, rather than those of physical force. 2 Chronicles 14:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
